    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.12), our highest-projected starter. He benefits from a confluence of favorable conditions against Merrill Kelly, including a significant dynamic platoon edge (+14%) and favorable wind direction (+10%). Crucially, his efficiency is boosted by Kelly\u2019s propensity for allowing stolen bases, a vital component of our strategy given the scarcity of that category. Joining him at the top of our output expectations is **Junior Caminero** (73.74), who anchors the middle of our lineup against Tyler Mahle, leveraging a strong SP skill matchup (+15%) to maintain an elite scoring profile. **Trea Turner** (67.99) also warrants high confidence; despite a slightly neutral park factor, his premium spot at the top of the order (+10%) ensures maximum plate appearances against Chris Paddack, keeping his daily efficiency well within our \"Strong\" tier.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves the bench, where **Jerar Encarnacion** (41.96) hovered just below our selection threshold. While **Jerar Encarnacion** benefits from a positive platoon advantage against Steven Matz, the optimizer ultimately favored the positional flexibility and higher cumulative scoring upside provided by **Hyeseong Kim** (55.99). **Hyeseong Kim** faces the difficult prospect of Dustin May, but his speed upside keeps him in the lineup despite a warning regarding May\u2019s elite ability to hold baserunners. Managers should keep a close watch on the status of **Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, and **Chase Meidroth**, as their scores are currently tethered to projected batting positions; should official lineups shift these players into lower-leverage spots, their marginal efficiency could dip toward our \"Below floor\" warning zone, potentially necessitating late swaps to preserve our precious game caps.",
